      "createdAt": "2026-03-26T06:22:55.607535+00:00",
      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, please don't apologize. It takes real courage to say this out loud, and the fact that you're telling me now — that matters. A lot.\n\nI also want to gently set something straight: you don't owe me honesty as a confession. You owe it to yourself, because *you're* the one doing the hard work here. So let's just move forward from this moment.\n\n---\n\nNow, I have to be straight with you about something important: **diagnosing what's happening with your foot and telling you how to treat it is genuinely outside what I can do for you.** I'm your running coach, not a physiotherapist or sports medicine doctor — and plantar fasciitis that's gotten worse with continued loading is exactly the kind of thing that needs a qualified clinician's eyes on it. Trying to guess at what's happening and prescribe treatment could make things significantly worse, and you deserve better than a guess.\n\n**What I'd strongly encourage you to do is contact your physiotherapist as soon as possible** — ideally this week — and tell them exactly what you told me: that the pain has increased, that you've had to stop runs early, and that it's been getting worse. They're the right person to assess what's going on and clear a path forward.\n\n---\n\nWhat *is* within my scope is this: **your training plan is paused until you've spoken with your physio.** Not as a punishment — as an investment in getting you back to running properly. Every day you protect that foot now is a day you're buying back for later.\n\nOnce you have guidance from them, I'll be right here to rebuild your plan around whatever they recommend. We've already shown you can run pain-free at a gentle effort — that foundation isn't gone.\n\n---\n\nOne question before you go: **Do you have easy access to your physiotherapist, or is there anything getting in the way of reaching out to them this week?**"
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_015hL1cZBSGaTGckbSc1gcsd"
    }
  ],
